  "format": "A live-to-tape watch-along of Damien Chazelle's 'Babylon.' Sean, Amanda, and Chris press play together and talk over all three-plus hours: the elephant, the Singin' in the Rain echoes, the closing montage, and whether it holds together outside a theater.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "The Watch-Along",
      "note": "press play with them",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Babylon",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "Chazelle's box-office flop, watched start to finish. The three agree it's a run of set pieces (the party, the Singin' in the Rain sound-stage homage, Tobey Maguire's underworld) without much connective tissue. Sean is in the hive, Chris hive-adjacent, Amanda admiring but out."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
